Package ca.ualberta.cs.team5geotopics

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AView<AModel>
    All Views implement this interface.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AModel<V extends AView>
    This is a generic Model class.
    BitmapJsonConverter
    Provides custom base64 serialization / deserialization for Bitmaps.
    BrowseActivity
    BrowseActivity is responsible for mainly handling the load of the comments.
    BrowseView
    BrowswView is responsible for loading the view of the comments.
    BrowseView.Holder
    Basic holder for the BrowseView containing comment parameteres.
    Cache
    Cache is what is responsible for saving and loading data to and from the user's device.
    CommentController
    The CommentController class is what helps distinguish between a new reply or a new top level comment.
    CommentListModel
    CommentListModel holds the sorting data and the functions to add a comment within the list.
    CommentModel
    CommentModel is the actual model for each and every comment.
    CommentSearch
    CommentSearch is used with respect to ElasticSearch and is called upon to help in matching string queries to/from the server for sorting.
    CreateCommentActivity
    Called when a user hits the '+' button at the top of any screen that has one.
    EditCommentActivity
    EditCommentActivity is called when a user is in the "My Comments" activity and selects that he/she wishes to edit a comment by clicking on it.
    ElasticSearchResponse<T>
    The ElasticSearchResponse helps in getting the correct source data for each comment.
    ElasticSearchSearchResponse<T>
    Responsible for getting the hits to a reference to a comment and gets the source of each comment from the CommentListController.
    GeoTopicsApplication
    This is a collection of singletons.
    GraphAdapterBuilder
    Writes a graph of objects as a list of named nodes.
    Hits<T>
    Hits returns the score and hits from an ElasticSearch response.
    InspectCommentActivity
    This source file holds the methods for the CreateCommentActivity as well as the EditCommentActivity.
    MyCommentsActivity
    Shown when a user clicks on "My Comments" from the start screen of the application In this activity, the user will be shown all of his/her comments including both top-level and reply comments.
    ReplyLevelActivity
    The view you see when you go to view the replies once you click a top level comment and click a reply.
    StartActivity
    Contains data for the start screen of the application.
    TopLevelActivity
    The view you see when you go to "Browse" from the start screen.
    User
    Holds all the data that the individual user whom is using the application creates/modifies.
